The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE FILM

 (Cartoon Network, noon, May 15) With the countdown on for the release of Book Six, it is time to refresh one?s memory with the first film of the series in which Harry (Daniel Radcliffe) sets off for Hogwarts to be trained as a wizard and meets friends Hermione and Ron. 

 THE SHOWCASE

 (Max Mueller Bhavan, 3 pm to 8 pm, till May 31)

 The series of small-scale drawings on Kalighat and miniature paintings by Stephen Weitzel tackles the issue of the same and the other. The work is a result of the artist?s trip to India last year. 

 THE WORKSHOP 

 (American Center, May 18-20, from 9.45 am on 18th, 2 pm onwards on 19th and 20th)

 The film appreciation workshop looks at new perspectives in three Hollywood genres ? comedy, action and sci-fi. The screening of Woody Allen?s Manhattan, Arthur Penn?s Bonny and Clyde and Don Siegel?s Invasion of the Body Snatchers will be followed by discussions.




